      "data": {
        "identity": {
          "graphId": "port-portal-ontology",
          "name": "Port / Portal Ontology",
          "version": "0.1.0",
          "description": "Plan graph for renaming view to port, port to portal, and adding real handle authorship to the new port node."
        },
        "intent": {
          "kind": "task",
          "scope": "local"
        },
        "declaration": {
          "targetMode": "artifact",
          "defaultSurfaceId": "minimap",
          "surfaces": []
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "port-portal-ontology-overview",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Overview",
      "position": {
        "x": -420,
        "y": -260
      },
      "width": 560,
      "height": 260,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "identity": {
          "graphId": "port-portal-ontology"
        },
        "markdown": "# Port / Portal Ontology\n\nThis graph keeps the rename and substrate work staged so we do not lose our place.\n\nCurrent target:\n- `declaration`\n- `markdown`\n- `port`\n- `portal`\n\nPlanned rename:\n- current `view` node -> `port`\n- current `port` node -> `portal`\n\nMissing substrate:\n- the new `port` must define real handles/ports, not just render a surface."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "port-portal-ontology-goal",
      "type": "goal",
      "label": "Make the ontology honest",
      "position": {
        "x": 200,
        "y": -260
      },
      "width": 380,
      "height": 220,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "identity": {
          "graphId": "port-portal-ontology"
        },
        "body": "Rename and re-ground the primitives so exposed surfaces are `ports`, opening/consuming nodes are `portals`, and the new port node actually authors real handles.",
        "priority": "critical",
        "status": "todo",
        "owner": "Michael",
        "estimateHours": "6",
        "acceptanceCriteria": [
          "The new port node authors at least a minimal handle schema",
          "The new portal node keeps current navigate and consume behavior",
          "Canonical docs and tutorials teach the renamed model"
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "port-portal-ontology-decision",
      "type": "decision",
      "label": "Rename direction",
      "position": {
        "x": -420,
        "y": 80
      },
      "width": 420,
      "height": 240,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "identity": {
          "graphId": "port-portal-ontology"
        },
        "question": "What are we renaming to what?",
        "status": "decided",
        "decision": "Current `view` becomes canonical `port`. Current `port` becomes canonical `portal`. Structural edge handles remain ports in the attachment sense.",
        "rationale": "This matches what the nodes actually do. The surface-bearing node is closer to a port, and the opening/consumer node is closer to a portal.",
        "consequences": [
          "The new port node must own handle definitions",
          "Portal remains a graph-visible opening, not a hidden setting",
          "Docs and tutorials need a coordinated language pass"
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "port-portal-ontology-open-question",
      "type": "open-question",
      "label": "Minimum handle authorship",
      "position": {
        "x": 60,
        "y": 80
      },
      "width": 420,
      "height": 240,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "identity": {
          "graphId": "port-portal-ontology"
        },
        "question": "What is the minimum V1 handle schema the new port node must author?",
        "status": "open",
        "owner": "Michael",
        "notes": "Likely minimum: one editable `root` handle, then optional additional handles with key, label, direction, dataType, and side/offset."
      }
    },
